    "citation": "Bouillon 2011 21256717",
    "population": "N: 22 Age: 6 months – 4 years",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“To determine the range of topiramate (TPM) concentrations obtained in children under 4 with the recommended dosage regimen (3—9 mg/kg/day) and to compare them to adult target ranges”",
    "covariates": "Tested: EI (enzyme inducer), WT, Age Included: EI (enzyme inducer), WT, Age",
    "observations": "TPM pharmacokinetics was described by a one-compartment model. EIAEDs increased the apparent clearance (CL/F) and age and body weight increased the apparent distribution volume (Vd/F). TPM dosage of 2/4 mg/kg/day (without/with EIEADs, respectively) provides the AUC reported in adults. In children under 4, alternative dosing regimen should be considered mainly when associated to EIAED to reach Ctrough comparable to adult values.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1-compartment model with first order absorption and elimination",
    "equations": "CL/F = theta1*EI+theta2*(1-EI) *exp(eta1) V/F = theta3*(WT/70)**theta4*(Age/2.34)**theta5*exp(eta2) Ka = theta6*exp(eta3) Tlag = theta7 Cobs = Cipred*(1+eps1)+eps2",
    "parameter_values": "Theta1 = 1.15 Theta2 = 0.608 Theta3 = 28.6 Theta4 = 0.686 Theta5 = 0.305 Theta6 = 1.04 Theta7 = 0.309 Omega1 = 0.0811 Omega2 = 0.0557 Omega3 = 1.29 COVomega2-3 = 0.263 Sigma1 = 0.00352 Sigma2 = 0.122",
    "validation": "Yes (VPC: 200 samples) / No"
